<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1090,1494]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis box="[206,358,1204,1229]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Distribution.</emphasis>
Endemic to Canary Islands and Madeira archipelago. MADEIRA: reported from many localities of southern and northern slopes (
<bibRefCitation author="Lindberg" box="[750,943,1242,1268]" pageId="17" pageNumber="27" refString="Lindberg, H. (1961) Hemiptera Insularum Madeirensium. Commentationes Biologicae, 24 (1), 1 - 82." type="journal article" year="1961">
Lindberg, 
<number box="[881,943,1242,1268]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1961.0">1961</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Quartau" box="[963,1314,1242,1268]" pageId="17" pageNumber="27" refString="Quartau, J. A. &amp; Fancony, A. I. (1988) On Eupteryx capreola Lindberg and E. filicum (Newman) (Homoptera: Cicadellidae, Typhlocybinae) from Madeira and the Azores. Boletim do Museu Municipal do Funchal, 40, 93 - 103." type="journal article" year="1988">
Quartau and Fançony, 
<number box="[1251,1314,1242,1268]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1988.0">1988</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<collectionCode box="[1342,1436,1242,1268]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">PORTO</collectionCode>
<collectionCode box="[206,308,1280,1306]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">SANTO</collectionCode>
: one locality (
<bibRefCitation author="Quartau" box="[472,801,1280,1306]" pageId="17" pageNumber="27" refString="Quartau, J. A. &amp; Fancony, A. I. (1988) On Eupteryx capreola Lindberg and E. filicum (Newman) (Homoptera: Cicadellidae, Typhlocybinae) from Madeira and the Azores. Boletim do Museu Municipal do Funchal, 40, 93 - 103." type="journal article" year="1988">
Quartau and Fançony, 
<number box="[738,801,1280,1306]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1988.0">1988</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1090,1494]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis box="[247,646,1318,1343]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
Food plants. 
<taxonomicName box="[402,646,1318,1343]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dennstaedtiaceae" genus="Pteridium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polypodiales" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aquilinum">Pteridium aquilinum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and herbaceous plants (
<bibRefCitation author="Quartau" box="[927,1256,1317,1343]" pageId="17" pageNumber="27" refString="Quartau, J. A. &amp; Fancony, A. I. (1988) On Eupteryx capreola Lindberg and E. filicum (Newman) (Homoptera: Cicadellidae, Typhlocybinae) from Madeira and the Azores. Boletim do Museu Municipal do Funchal, 40, 93 - 103." type="journal article" year="1988">
Quartau and Fançony, 
<number box="[1193,1256,1317,1343]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1988.0">1988</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[247,357,1355,1380]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Quartau" box="[365,706,1355,1381]" pageId="17" pageNumber="27" refString="Quartau, J. A. &amp; Fancony, A. I. (1988) On Eupteryx capreola Lindberg and E. filicum (Newman) (Homoptera: Cicadellidae, Typhlocybinae) from Madeira and the Azores. Boletim do Museu Municipal do Funchal, 40, 93 - 103." type="journal article" year="1988">
Quartau and Fançony (
<number box="[636,697,1355,1381]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1988.0">1988</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
suggested that 
<taxonomicName authority="Lindberg, 1954" authorityName="Lindberg" authorityYear="1954" box="[889,1296,1355,1381]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Eupteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capreola">
<emphasis box="[889,1107,1355,1380]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Eupteryx capreola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lindberg" box="[1115,1296,1355,1381]" pageId="17" pageNumber="27" refString="Lindberg, H. (1954) Hemiptera Insularum Canariensium, Systematik, Okologie und Verbreitung der Kanarischen Heteropteren und Cicadinen. Commentationes Biologicae, 14 (1), 1953 (issued 1954), 1 - 304." type="journal article" year="1954">
Lindberg, 
<number box="[1237,1296,1355,1381]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1954.0">1954</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is probably an extreme form of 
<taxonomicName authority="Newman, 1853" authorityName="Newman" authorityYear="1853" box="[482,887,1393,1419]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Eupteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="filicum">
<emphasis box="[482,676,1393,1418]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Eupteryx filicum</emphasis>
(Newman, 
<number box="[815,878,1393,1419]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1853.0">1853</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
. More recent morphological studies and population dynamics analysis of populations on 
<taxonomicName box="[768,918,1431,1456]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dennstaedtiaceae" genus="Pteridium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polypodiales" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aquilinum">
<emphasis box="[768,918,1431,1456]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P. aquilinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also failed to separate this species from 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Eupteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="filicum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">E. filicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Aveiro" box="[343,736,1468,1494]" pageId="17" pageNumber="26" refString="Aveiro, M. J. &amp; Aguin-Pombo, D. (2003 a) Population dynamics of Eupteryx leafhoppers on Pteridium aquilinum ferns in Madeira. How many species do we have? II Symposium of Island Ecosystems, Funchal, Madeira 5 - 9 th October 2003, 71." type="journal article" year="2003" yearSuffix="a">
Aveiro and Aguin-Pombo, 
<number box="[662,723,1468,1494]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="2003.0">2003</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Aguin-Pombo" box="[748,826,1468,1494]" pageId="17" pageNumber="26" refString="Aveiro, M. J. &amp; Aguin-Pombo, D. (2003 b) Large morphological variation in island populations of Eupteryx leafhoppers from Madeira Island. II Symposium of Island Ecosystems, Funchal, Madeira, 5 - 9 th October 2003, 54." type="journal article" year="2003" yearSuffix="b">
<number box="[748,811,1468,1494]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="2003.0">2003</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
). The status of this species needs to be confirmed.
</paragraph>
